<subSubSection id="C3246572FF9FC931FF62F8F0FE04FE82" lastPageId="63" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF9FC930FF62F8F0FA12F81E" blockId="62.[151,1437,1626,2013]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9FC930FF62F8F0FDCBF857" bold="true" box="[199,581,1914,1941]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
Description. Female (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF9FC930FE6FF8F0FDB6F857" box="[458,568,1914,1940]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 10.8. Prosoma 3.9 long, 3.7 wide. Opisthosoma 6.5 long, 4.1 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.34, 0.25, 0.19, 0.23; interdistances: 0.25, 0.20, 0.48, 0.41, 0.25, 0.19. Legs: I: 19.4 (5.3, 2.1, 5.2, 5.3, 1.5); II: 20.3 (5.7, 2.2, 5.5, 5.4, 1.5); III: 14.4 (4.3, 1.6, 3.7, 3.5, 1.3); IV: 16.1 (4.6, 1.5, 4.2, 4.4, 1.4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF9EC931FF32FF1DFE84FEDE" blockId="63.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
Spination follows the generic pattern. Epigyne: EF wider than long, MAB short and narrow; MS drop-shaped, with lateral margins gently converging anteriorly; LL almost touching posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9EC931FBA0FF31FBE6FF16" box="[1029,1128,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 253–259" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1813,1837]" captionTargetBox="[163,1422,393,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-80@63.[154,1434,381,1790]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 253–259. 253–256 Meri tambor spec. nov., male (INPA 3522), left palp (253 prolateral, 254 ventral, 255 retrolateral, 256 detail of embolus); 257–259 Meri tapirapeco spec. nov., female (INPA) (257 epigyne, 258 vulva, 259 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP— epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; tp—tegular protrusion. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550500/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 257</figureCitation>
). Vulva: GP slightly longer than wide, mediad, arising from ducts at first turn; SP irregular-shaped, with folds; FD antero laterad (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9EC931FB59FF55FA16FF3A" box="[1276,1432,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 250–252" captionStartId="61.[151,264,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[189,1403,1171,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-364@61.[181,1406,1166,1915]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES 250–252. Meri sanctivincenti (Simon) comb. nov., female (250 epigyne, 251 vulva, 252 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn of duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale line: 1 mm. Modified from Jäger 2020 (94: figs 349–351)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550498/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Figs 251–252</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9EC931FF32FE88FF71FEDE" box="[151,255,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 253–259" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1813,1837]" captionTargetBox="[163,1422,393,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-80@63.[154,1434,381,1790]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 253–259. 253–256 Meri tambor spec. nov., male (INPA 3522), left palp (253 prolateral, 254 ventral, 255 retrolateral, 256 detail of embolus); 257–259 Meri tapirapeco spec. nov., female (INPA) (257 epigyne, 258 vulva, 259 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP— epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; tp—tegular protrusion. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550500/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">256–257</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF9EC931FF62FEADFE04FE82" blockId="63.[151,1437,151,357]" box="[199,394,295,321]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9EC931FF62FEADFE83FE82" bold="true" box="[199,269,295,321]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Male:</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF9EC931FF62FEC0FCE4FEA6" box="[199,874,330,357]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF9EC931FF62FEC0FCE4FEA6" blockId="63.[151,1437,151,357]" box="[199,874,330,357]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
